<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-01-03T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-01-03T18:00:00-05:00" n="254" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d254">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.5151/782: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-01-03T18:00:00-05:00">January 3, 1936—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2. Your 346, December 21, 1 p.m.<note n="32" xml:id="d254fn32"><ref target="frus1935v04#pg_386"><hi rend="italic">Ibid</hi>., p.
                                    386</ref>.</note> Please inquire of the Minister of Foreign
                                Affairs<note n="33" xml:id="d254fn33">José Carlos de Macedo
                                Soares.</note> and, in your discretion, of the Minister of
                                Finance,<note n="34" xml:id="d254fn34">Arthur de Souza Costa.</note>
                            whether the Brazilian Government has completed arrangements for funds to
                            make a cash payment to the American owners of frozen credits equivalent
                            to that promised the British creditors. Please cable.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>